\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The intention of this program is to create a task manager for the DAW Reaper.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Create a GUI that organizes all important information and operations in as simple a manner as possible.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The GUI must be able to do the following:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab create a list of tasks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab create sub-tasks of potentially infinite depth\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab tasks with subtasks can be collapsed so only the parent is shown\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab undo/redo each and every operation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab be dockable within reaper\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The task list can be optionally defined to be per-project, per-project-version, per-selected-track per-selected-item\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The task list will be context-dependent based on current user action\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab when a task is selected, if a task list for that track exist, display it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab when a item is selected, if a task list for that item exists, display it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab if nothing else, display the project task list\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab There is an input bar at the bottom of the task list\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab this bar will take all keyboard input for the window so that you dont need to worry about clicking the input bar before you type into it. As long as reatask is the focused window, just start typing and press enter to create a task\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 INTERFACE:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab middle clicking a task will delete it\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab right clicking anywhere on the task list will open a settings menu\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab right clicking on the input bar will perform an undo\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab shift+right click will perform a redo\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab double clicking a task will collapse/expand its children (if they exist)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab pressing enter will take the current text in the input bar and create a sibling task\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab pressing Tab will take the current text in the input bar and create a child task\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Pressing Shift+Tab will take the current text in the input bar and create a parent task\sa180\par}
}
